a. Configure Email using UiPath (IMAP/SMTP)
This configuration allows UiPath to talk to servers like Gmail, Outlook.com, or Yahoo.
Open UiPath Studio: Create a new Process.
Check Activities: In the Activities panel, search for "IMAP". If not found, go to Manage Packages > All Packages and install UiPath.Mail.Activities.
Drag Activity: Drag the Get IMAP Mail Messages activity into the Designer panel.
Enter Server Details: In the Properties panel:
Port: 993 (for IMAP) or 465/587 (for SMTP).
Server: "imap.gmail.com" or your specific provider's server address.
Logins: Enter your email address and App Password (not your regular login password) in quotes.

b. Read Emails
Once configured, you need to extract the emails into a format the bot can understand.
Define Folder: In the Get IMAP Mail Messages properties, set MailFolder to "Inbox".
Filter Settings: Check the box for OnlyUnreadMessages if you only want new mail.
Set Limit: Set the Top property to 5 to read only the five most recent emails.
Create Output Variable: In the Messages field of the Properties panel, press Ctrl + K and name the variable mailList.

Note: This creates a variable of type List<MailMessage>.

View Output: Drag a For Each activity. Set the type argument to System.Net.Mail.MailMessage and the input to mailList. Inside, use a Log Message activity with item.Subject to see the titles in the Output console.

c. Send Email with Attachment
Sending an email requires the SMTP activity (or Outlook activity if the desktop app is installed).
Drag Activity: Search for and drag the Send SMTP Mail Message activity.
Configure Recipients: Fill in the To, Subject, and Body fields (all text must be in double quotes).
Attach File: * In the Properties panel, click the "..." (ellipses) next to Attachments.
Click Create Argument.
In the Value field, provide the full file path: "C:\Users\Name\Documents\Report.pdf".
Port/Server: Enter "smtp.gmail.com" and port 465. Ensure the Secure Connection (SSL) is set to Auto or SSL.

d. Save Email Attachments & Reply to Email
These actions are performed inside a loop to process individual emails.

Save Attachments
Inside For Each Loop: Drag the Save Attachments activity.
Set Input: In the Message property, type item (the current mail object from your loop).
Folder Path: Create a folder on your desktop and provide that path in the FolderPath property (e.g., "C:\SavedAttachments\").

Reply to Email
Drag Activity: Place the Reply To Mail Message activity after the Save Attachment activity.
Reference Original: In the MailMessage property, enter item.
Compose Reply: Type your message in the Body field (e.g., "Hello, I have received your attachment and saved it. - Bot").
Optional: Check ReplyEntireSession if you wish to "Reply All" to everyone in the thread.
